\begin{gather*}
A-\lambda{I}=\begin{bmatrix}6-\lambda&9\\-4&-6-\lambda\end{bmatrix}.
\end{gather*}
\begin{align*}
p(\lambda)&=|A-\lambda{I}|=\begin{vmatrix}6-\lambda&9\\-4&-6-\lambda\end{vmatrix}.\\
&=(6-\lambda)(-6-\lambda)-(-4\times9)\\
&=-36+0\lambda+\lambda^2+36\\
&=\lambda^2+0\lambda+0\\
&=(\lambda+0)(\lambda+0)
\end{align*}
Solving $p(\lambda)=0$ yields the eigenvalues $\lambda_1=0$ and $\lambda_2=0$.
Find the eigenvalues of \(\begin{bmatrix}6&9\\-4&-6\end{bmatrix}\).
$\lambda_1=0,\lambda_2=0$
